nt part of each overview article. Among the essays in the first volume are overview articles dealing with VP ellipsis (by Kyle Johnson), Ergativity (by Alana Johns), tone (by San Duanmu), acquisition of phonology (by Paula Fikkert), and semantic change (by Elizabeth Closs Traugott). The second volume offers articles on subjects ranging from the development of grammars (by David Lightfoot) and markedness in phonology (by Keren Rice) to the syntactic representation of linguistic events (by Sara Thomas Rosen), optionality in Optimality syntax (by Gereon Müller) and the nature of coordination (by Ljiljana Progovac).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAufsatzsammlung. 4aLinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBooij, Geert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurzio, Luigi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCheng, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCheng, Lisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCornell, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuanmu, San, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEubank, Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFikkert, Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoekstra, Teun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoop, Helen de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHornstein, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohns, Alana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Kyle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 